{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a452e87e-84a3-4f05-b28e-376ef391a0e1","content":"For a **Web API project**, here are your main options:\n\n### Templates\n| Template | Command |\n|---|---|\n| ASP.NET Core Web API | `dotnet new webapi` |\n| ASP.NET Core Minimal API | `dotnet new webapi --use-minimal-apis` |\n| ASP.NET Core API (controllers) | `dotnet new webapi --use-controllers` |\n\n### Authentication Options (`--auth`)\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n### Example\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --use-controllers -o MyApi\n```\n\nYou can also add **JWT Bearer** or **Identity** auth manually via NuGet packages (`Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer`, `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Identity`).\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a project with a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fa88e02f-3906-4cd3-8e05-fcc6993da252","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context) or web development in general. Let me answer based on my knowledge without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":336,"requestId":"0414:1B1922:A91B04:D2AD53:6A01294E"},"id":"d5ecff20-b897-4ac1-a693-7e274eabd691","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:56:52.986Z","parentId":"c1b48795-4ff4-4a60-936c-b96e47b3e99a"}
